A towering bamboo forest bending gracefully in a powerful storm, rendered in Studio Ghibli's signature warm, hand-painted animation style. In the foreground, a solitary figure sits cross-legged on a mossy rock in deep meditation, completely calm despite the swirling wind and rain around them. The bamboo stalks curve dramatically but remain unbroken, their jade-green leaves creating sweeping arcs across a turbulent sky painted in deep purples and grays with breaks of golden light. Mist swirls between the bamboo stems, and small glowing particles drift through the air like floating embers. The figure's robes ripple gently, suggesting inner stillness amidst outer chaos. Soft, diffused lighting creates depth and atmosphere, with careful attention to the organic textures of bark, moss, and weathered stone characteristic of Miyazaki's environmental storytelling.
